  "local_port": 33510,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some karaoke songs for a 2nd alto?",
  "response": "Choosing the right karaoke song as a 2nd alto can be a fun challenge. 2nd altos often have rich, lower-register voices that can really shine with the right song choice. Here are some great karaoke songs that would suit a 2nd alto voice:\n\n### Pop/Rock\n1. **Adele - \"Rolling in the Deep\"**\n   - Adele's powerful lower register makes this song perfect for a 2nd alto.\n2. **Billie Eilish - \"Bad Guy\"**\n   - Billie's lower tones and the song's catchy beat are great for showing off a 2nd alto range.\n3. **Lorde - \"Royals\"**\n   - Lorde's deep voice and the song's melody work well for 2nd altos.\n4. **Florence + The Machine - \"Shake It Out\"**\n   - Florence Welch\u2019s powerful voice has a lot of range, but the lower parts of this song are particularly suited to 2nd altos.\n\n### R&B/Soul\n1. **Alicia Keys - \"Fallin'\"**\n   - This song showcases the richness of a 2nd alto voice with its soulful melody.\n2. **Etta James - \"At Last\"**\n   - A classic that allows 2nd altos to show off their depth and emotion.\n3. **Amy Winehouse - \"Valerie\"**\n   - Amy's unique voice and the song's soulful vibe are perfect for 2nd altos.\n\n### Country\n1. **Carrie Underwood - \"Before He Cheats\"**\n   - The lower parts of this song are great for 2nd altos to belt out.\n2. **Dolly Parton - \"Jolene\"**\n   - Dolly\u2019s lower register in this song is perfect for a 2nd alto to showcase.\n\n### Musical Theater\n1. **\"Defying Gravity\" from Wicked (Elphaba's part)**\n   - While challenging, the lower parts of this song can be great for a 2nd alto to showcase their range.\n2. **\"I Dreamed a Dream\" from Les Mis\u00e9rables**\n   - Fantine\u2019s haunting melody is perfect for a 2nd alto\u2019s rich tones.\n\n### Classic Rock\n1. **Heart - \"Barracuda\"**\n   - Ann Wilson\u2019s powerful voice and the song's energy are great for 2nd altos.\n2. **Stevie Nicks - \"Edge of Seventeen\"**\n   - Stevie\u2019s lower tones in this song work well for 2nd altos.\n\n### Jazz/Blues\n1. **Nina Simone - \"Feeling Good\"**\n   - Nina\u2019s deep, soulful voice makes this song perfect for 2nd altos.\n2. **Billie Holiday - \"God Bless the Child\"**\n   - Billie\u2019s rich, emotive voice is ideal for a 2nd alto to emulate.\n\nWhen choosing a karaoke song, consider the key of the song and whether it suits your vocal range. Don\u2019t hesitate to transpose the song if needed to better fit your voice. Most importantly, pick a song that you enjoy and feel confident singing!",
